{Before going into the theory of the various sidelines against 1.d4 Nf6, we
are going to study typical strategies and pawn structures. This will improve
our all-round understanding and greatly help us understand the strategic basis
of various theoretical lines. In our lecture we will deal with the following
themes: - 1) Minority attacks in Hedgehog setups against the London System and
Torre Attack. 2) Typical mistakes in the Jobava System 3) Typical strategies
in the Colle System 4) The strategical basics of the line 1.d4 Nf6 2.Nf3 e6 3.
g3 b5.}  *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "SETUPS VS LONDON & TORRE"]
[Black "MINORITY ATTACK"]
[Result "*"]
[Annotator "GM Ioannis Papaioannou"]
[PlyCount "20"]
[EventDate "2024.06.07"]

1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bf4 {Against both, the Torre Attack and the London
System, we use setups in the style of the Hedgehog. We will often reach
positions where we can play for a minority attack and consequently will study
a number of games with this theme.} (3. Bg5) 3... c5 4. e3 cxd4 5. exd4 b6 6.
c3 Bb7 7. Bd3 Be7 8. Nbd2 d6 9. O-O O-O 10. Re1 Nbd7 {[%cal Ya7a6,Yf8e8]} *

[Event "4NCL 2013-14"]
[Site "Hinckley ENG"]
