1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 e6 3. e3 c5 4. Nf3 cxd4 5. exd4 Be7 6. Bd3 O-O 7. O-O d6 8.
Nc3 b6 9. Ne4 Bb7 10. Qe2 a6 11. Rfe1 Nxe4 12. Bxe4 Bxe4 13. Qxe4 d5 ({In my
view} 13... Nd7 {would have been even better.} 14. c3 (14. d5 $2 {loses a pawn.
} Nf6 $17 (14... e5 $15 {would also be fine strategically.})) ({How should
Black continue after} 14. c4 {? The best move is} d5 $1 {and after} 15. cxd5 {
we collect the d5-pawn with our knight:} Nf6 $1 16. Qe2 Nxd5 17. Bg3 Bd6 18.
Ne5 Bxe5 $1 19. dxe5 Qd7 $15) 14... Nf6 15. Qe2 b5 16. a4 Qb6) 14. Qd3 Nc6 {
I would think that Black may be slightly better in this position.} 15. Ne5 Nxe5
16. Bxe5 Bf6 17. Qf3 Bxe5 18. Rxe5 {In this positon Black is slightly better
due to the upcoming minority attack. However, we must not forget about the
safety of our king!} Qc7 $2 {Stepping away from the kingside with the queen is
a mistake.} (18... Rc8 $1 {we should better keep our queen on d8 for while....
to protect our kingsde !!} 19. c3 b5 $15 20. Rae1 (20. a4 b4 $1 21. cxb4 Qb6
$17 {[%csl Rb2,Rb4,Rd4][%cal Yb6d4,Yb6b4]}) 20... a5 {If White tries to attack,
our queen is ready to help out in the defence!} 21. Rh5 g6 (21... b4 $5) 22.
Rh6 Kg7 23. Qh3 Rh8 {We defend the kingside and attack with ...b4 on the
queenside. If White fails to deliver mate, his pieces will turn out to be
misplaced.} 24. Re5 b4 (24... Qf6 25. Reh5)) 19. c3 b5 20. Rae1 Qc4 $2 {
Stepping away even further from the kingside.} (20... a5) (20... b4 $5 21. cxb4
Qc4) 21. b3 Qc7 22. Rg5 Kh8 23. Rh5 Kg8 24. Re3 $36 f5 $2 (24... Rac8 25. Qh3
h6 26. Rxh6 $1 gxh6 27. Qxh6 $18) (24... g6 25. Rxh7 $1 Kxh7 26. Qf6 $1 $18 {
[%cal Ye3h3]}) (24... Qd6 $1 25. Qg4 f5 $14) 25. Rxe6 $16 Qf7 26. Re5 g6 27.
Rh3 Rae8 28. Qf4 Qc7 29. Rd3 b4 30. Qe3 f4 31. Qe1 Rxe5 32. dxe5 Re8 33. cxb4
Rxe5 34. Qd2 Qc2 35. h3 Qb1+ 36. Kh2 Re1 37. g3 f3 38. g4 Re2 39. Qc3 Rxf2+ 40.
Kg3 Rg2+ 41. Kh4 Rc2 42. Qe5 Qc1 43. Qxd5+ Kg7 44. Qe5+ Kf8 45. Rd8+ Kf7 46.
Rd7+ 1-0

