1. d4 d5 ({We can reach the position from the game with} 1... Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3.
Bf4 c5 4. e3) 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. e3 c5 4. Nc3 e6 $2 {A typical mistake in the Bf4
Veresov (or Jobava London System). We must avoid this!} 5. Nb5 $1 $16 Na6 {
Black can defend against Nc7 without difficulties, but now it's no longer
possible to get rid of the annoying knight on b5.} 6. c3 Be7 (6... Bd7 7. a4 c4
8. b3 cxb3 9. Qxb3 $16) 7. a4 O-O 8. h4 $1 {15 years ago such chess didn't
exist: playing a4 and h4 in the very first moves...} (8. Nf3 Nh5 {If Black
manages to exchange the dark-squared bishop, he will again be able to move the
a6-knight and play ...a6.} 9. Bg3 Nxg3 10. hxg3 Nb8) 8... Ne4 9. Bd3 Bd7 10.
Nf3 f6 11. Qc2 Bc6 12. Nd2 cxd4 13. Nxd4 Bd7 14. Nxe4 dxe4 15. Bxe4 e5 16.
Bxh7+ Kh8 17. Bg6 Qc8 18. Nf5 exf4 19. Nxe7 Qc5 20. O-O-O Bg4 21. Nd5 Rad8 22.
Nxf4 Bxd1 23. Rxd1 Qe5 24. Bd3 Qc5 25. b4 Nxb4 26. cxb4 Qxc2+ 27. Kxc2 1-0

