1. d4 d5 ({Our move order would be} 1... Nf6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Bf4) 2. Bf4 Nf6 3.
Nc3 e6 4. e3 c5 $2 {Again this mistake by a very high-level player!} (4... Be7
5. Bd3 O-O 6. Nf3 c5 7. dxc5 (7. Ne5 c4 8. Be2 Nc6 9. g4) 7... Bxc5 8. O-O Nc6
9. e4 dxe4 10. Nxe4 Nxe4 11. Bxe4 Qxd1 12. Rfxd1 (12. Raxd1)) 5. Nb5 $1 $16 Na6
6. h3 {Stopping any ...Nh5-ideas before developing the knight to f3.} Be7 7.
Nf3 Ne4 8. c3 c4 9. a4 Bd7 10. Nd2 Nxd2 11. Qxd2 O-O 12. b3 $1 $14 {An
important move in this structure!} cxb3 13. Qb2 Qa5 {Black is under some
pressure and cannot get rid of the b5-knight.} (13... Nb8 14. Nc7 $18) (13...
Rc8 14. Nxa7 $18) 14. Be2 Rfc8 15. O-O Nb8 16. Qxb3 Qb6 17. a5 Qc6 18. Rfc1 Na6
19. c4 $18 {White has a strong initiative on the queenside.} h6 20. c5 Be8 21.
Nd6 Bxd6 22. Bxd6 Nc7 23. Rab1 Rab8 24. Qd3 a6 25. Rb6 Qd7 26. Rcb1 Na8 27.
R6b2 Nc7 28. Rxb7 Rxb7 29. Rxb7 Qc6 30. Rxc7 Rxc7 31. Bxc7 Qxc7 32. Qxa6 Qb8
33. Qb6 Qa8 34. a6 Kh7 35. Qb7 Bc6 36. Qxa8 Bxa8 37. Bb5 1-0

