{A VERY good game by Black demonstrating typical plans in the structure with
Bxf6 exf6!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 d5 3. Bxf6 exf6 4. e3 Bd6 5. c4 dxc4 6. Bxc4 O-O
7. Nc3 c6 8. Nf3 f5 9. O-O (9. Qc2 Nd7 $1 {is possible and it's the move we
want to play. White cannot take on f5.} 10. O-O (10. Qxf5 $4 Ne5 $19) 10... Nf6
11. Rad1 (11. Ne5 $2 Bxe5 12. dxe5 Ng4 $17 {[%csl Re5]}) 11... Qe7 {Taking e5
under control.} (11... Bd7 12. Ne5 {could be annoying.}) 12. Rfe1 {Is White
intending e4?} (12. d5 c5 $1 13. Nb5 Bd7 $15) 12... Bd7 {It turns out that
White does not really have a threat:} 13. e4 $2 fxe4 14. Nxe4 Nxe4 (14... Bf5
$2 15. Nxd6 $1 Bxc2 16. Rxe7 Bxd1 17. Ne5 $14) 15. Rxe4 $2 Bf5 $1 (15... Qf6 {
If tactics did not work, then Black would have no problems after this simple
move.}) 16. Rxe7 Bxc2 $19 {and Black wins material.}) 9... Nd7 10. Qc2 Nf6 11.
Rad1 g6 ({I would have played} 11... Qe7 {first, for example} 12. d5 (12. a3
Bd7 13. d5 c5 14. h3 (14. Nb5 Bxb5 15. Bxb5 g6) 14... g6 15. Bb5 Rac8 (15...
Bc8 16. a4 a6 17. Bc4 Bd7 18. Rfe1 Rfe8 (18... Rad8 19. e4 Nxe4 20. Nxe4 fxe4
21. Rxe4 (21. Qxe4) 21... Qf6))) 12... c5 13. Nb5 Bd7 14. Nxd6 Qxd6) 12. d5 b5
$3 {This is based on tactics! Black wins a pawn.} (12... c5 $1 $15 {was also
simple and good!}) 13. Be2 $5 (13. Bb3 b4 14. Ne2 (14. Na4) 14... cxd5 15. Ned4
(15. Bxd5 $2 Nxd5 16. Rxd5 Bxh2+ $19) 15... Bb7 16. Qe2 a6 17. g3 Qe7 18. Rc1
Rac8) 13... b4 14. Na4 cxd5 $17 15. Nd4 Bd7 16. Bf3 (16. Nb5 Bxb5 17. Bxb5
Bxh2+ 18. Kxh2 Qb8+ (18... Ng4+ 19. Kh3 Qb8 $19) 19. Kg1 Qxb5 $19) 16... Rc8
17. Qb3 Qa5 $19 0-1

