{Another good game (of mine) in the Trompowsky with Bxf6 exf6.} 1. d4 Nf6 2.
Bg5 d5 3. Bxf6 (3. Nd2 c6 4. Ngf3 Bf5 5. e3 Nbd7 6. c4 Qb6 $5) 3... exf6 4. e3
Bd6 5. c4 (5. Nf3 O-O (5... Be6 $6 6. Nbd2 O-O 7. c4 dxc4 8. Bxc4 Bxc4 9. Nxc4)
) 5... dxc4 6. Bxc4 O-O 7. Ne2 f5 8. g3 Nd7 9. Qc2 Nf6 10. Nbc3 c6 11. O-O Bd7
12. Rad1 Qe7 $15 {White fights for equality in this line - that's why we are
studying it.} 13. Nf4 g6 (13... Bxf4 14. gxf4 Rfe8) 14. Rfe1 Rfe8 $15 (14... h5
$4 15. Nxg6 $18) (14... Rad8 {was also possible since e4 is not a threat.} 15.
