{A great game by Black - both in the opening and the endgame! Amazing
technique!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 d5 3. Bxf6 exf6 4. e3 Bd6 5. g3 O-O 6. Bg2 c6 7.
Ne2 Be6 $5 {This is playable now - after a later c4, White no longer has the
option to play Bxc4 after ...dxc4. This is important since exchanging bishops
would be in White's favour!} (7... f5 $1 {with the idea to play ...Nd7-f6, is
simple and good!} 8. O-O Nd7 9. Nd2 Nf6 10. b3 (10. c4 dxc4 11. Nxc4 Bc7 $11)
10... Be6 11. c4 g6 12. cxd5 cxd5 $15 {Even accepting an isolated pawn is fine
for Black in this position. This is an exception and it works, because White's
pieces are strangely placed.} (12... Nxd5 $15 {is the usual way to recapture.})
) 8. O-O Nd7 9. Qd3 f5 10. Nd2 Nf6 11. c4 Qe7 12. Rfc1 (12. cxd5 cxd5 $5 $15 {
is again fully satisfactory.} (12... Nxd5)) 12... g6 13. a3 (13. c5 Bc7 14. b4
h5 $132 {White attacks on the queenside and Black starts his counterplay on
the kingside.}) 13... Rfd8 14. b4 Ne4 15. c5 Bc7 16. a4 h5 17. b5 h4 $15 {
Black has strong counterplay.} 18. Rcb1 Rab8 19. b6 axb6 20. cxb6 Bd6 21. a5
Kg7 22. a6 bxa6 23. Rxa6 Bc8 24. Ra7 Rd7 25. Rxd7 Qxd7 26. Nc3 Qd8 27. Na4 Ba6
$1 28. Qc2 Bb5 $17 29. Nxe4 fxe4 30. Bf1 Bxa4 31. Qxa4 hxg3 32. hxg3 Rxb6 33.
Rxb6 Qxb6 34. Qa8 Qc7 35. Kg2 Qd7 36. Be2 Be7 37. Bd1 c5 38. dxc5 Bxc5 39. Bb3
Qf5 40. Qxd5 Qf3+ 41. Kg1 Bxe3 42. Qe5+ f6 43. Qc7+ Kh6 44. fxe3 Qxe3+ 45. Kh2
Qf2+ 46. Kh3 Qf1+ 47. Kh2 e3 48. Bc4 e2 49. Qc5 Qe1 50. Qd4 Qf1 51. Bxe2 Qxe2+
52. Kg1 Qf3 53. Kh2 (53. Qh4+ Kg7 54. Kh2 (54. Qh3 Qd1+ 55. Kh2 Qd2+ 56. Kg1
Qd3) 54... Qf2+ 55. Kh3 Qg1) 53... Qe2+ 54. Kg1 Qe5 55. Qh4+ Kg7 56. Qg4 Qe3+
57. Kg2 Qd2+ 58. Kg1 Qd3 59. Qf4 g5 60. Qb8 Qf3 61. Kh2 Qe2+ 62. Kg1 Kg6 63.
Qc8 (63. Qg8+ Kh5 64. Qf7+ Kg4 65. Qxf6 Qe1+ 66. Kg2 Qxg3+ 67. Kh1 Qf3+) 63...
f5 64. Qd7 (64. Qh8 Qe6 (64... Qa2 65. Kf1) 65. Kg2 (65. Qd4)) 64... Qe3+ (
64... Qe4 65. Kh2 Kh5 66. Qh7+ Kg4 67. Qh3+ Kf3 68. Qf1+ Ke3 69. Qc1+ Kd4 70.
Qb1 g4 71. Qb6+ Kd3 72. Qb5+) 65. Kg2 Qe4+ 66. Kh2 Qc2+ 67. Kg1 Kh5 68. Qd4 Qe2
69. Qb4 Qe3+ 70. Kh2 Qf2+ 71. Kh1 Qxg3 72. Qe7 Qf3+ 73. Kh2 Kg4 74. Qa7 Qe2+
75. Kh1 f4 76. Qd4 Kg3 {0-1 (77) Andreikin,D (2696)-Tomashevsky,E (2707)
Khanty-Mansiysk 2011} 0-1

