1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 d5 3. Bxf6 exf6 4. e3 Be6 {This move is premature in my
opinion.} 5. g3 {Now the inaccuracy 4...Be6 is without consequence.} ({For
example} 5. Nd2 Nd7 6. c4 dxc4 7. Bxc4 {and exchanging the bishops is in
White's favour.}) 5... Nd7 6. Bg2 Bd6 7. Ne2 f5 8. Nd2 O-O 9. b3 Nf6 10. c4 c6
11. O-O (11. cxd5 cxd5 $5 $15) 11... Ne4 $15 12. c5 (12. Rc1 h5) (12. cxd5 cxd5
$1 13. Nf4 Bxf4 $1 14. gxf4 Rc8 $17) 12... Bc7 13. Qc2 (13. Nf4 Bd7 $1 $15 (
13... Bxf4 14. exf4 $11)) 13... h5 14. b4 (14. h4 f6 $1 {[%cal Yg7g5]} (14...
g5 15. hxg5 Qxg5 16. Nf3 Qh6 $13) 15. Nf4 Bf7 $36 {[%cal Yg7g5]}) 14... h4 15.
a4 hxg3 ({We should not play} 15... a6 $2 {unless we stop his play on the
queenside (which isn't the case).}) 16. hxg3 g5 $17 {[%cal Yg8g7,Yf8h8,Yd8f6]
Black's attack is very dangerous.} 17. b5 Kg7 18. bxc6 bxc6 19. Nf3 Bc8 $1 {
Activating the bishop.} 20. Ne5 Qe8 21. Nd3 Ba6 22. Rfe1 Qe6 23. Bf3 Rh8 24.
Nb4 ({White cannot play the otherwise desireable} 24. Kg2 {due to} g4 $19)
24... Qh6 25. Bg2 Bc4 26. Rab1 Bxg3 0-1

