1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 d5 3. Bxf6 exf6 4. e3 Nd7 $5 {A VERY GOOD MOVE ORDER FOR
BLACK, ALTHOUGH THERE IS NOTHING WRONG WITH 4...Bd6.} 5. Bd3 c6 6. Nd2 (6. Qf3
g6 7. g4 (7. Nd2 f5) 7... h5 8. h3 (8. gxh5 Rxh5) 8... Nb6 9. gxh5 Rxh5 $17)
6... Bd6 7. c3 (7. Qf3 g6 8. g4 h5 $1) 7... g6 $1 {When we see Bd3, we
postpone castling until White shows his hand!} (7... O-O $2 8. Qf3 g6 9. g4 Nb6
10. Ne2 $16) 8. Qf3 $2 (8. Ngf3 $1 {White must switch to positional play!} O-O
9. O-O f5 10. c4 Nf6 (10... dxc4) 11. cxd5 cxd5 $5 $15 (11... Nxd5 $36)) (8. g4
$2 h5) 8... f5 $1 $15 (8... O-O $2 9. g4 $1 $40) 9. Ne2 Nf6 10. h3 h5 11. c4
Ne4 $17 {White's pieces are misplaced - Black is even threatening ...Ng5,
winning the queen.} 12. Nc3 Be6 13. cxd5 cxd5 14. Qd1 O-O 15. Rc1 Qg5 16. O-O
Nxd2 17. Qxd2 f4 18. e4 Bxh3 19. f3 Be6 20. Rfe1 Rad8 21. exd5 Bxd5 22. Nxd5
