1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4 Bd7 4. e3 e6 5. Nb5 Bxb5 6. Bxb5+ c6 ({or} 6... Nbd7
) 7. Bd3 Bd6 8. Bg5 (8. Nf3 {This strategy, known from the London System,
works well for White when Black has a bishop on c8.} Bxf4 9. exf4 c5 {Here
Black has a good position with no bad pieces.}) 8... Nbd7 9. Nf3 e5 $11 10. Bf5
(10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Nxe5 Bxe5 12. c3 h6 13. Bh4 Qe7 $5 {We may consider
castling long in connection with ...g5, e.g.} 14. O-O g5 15. Bg3 Bxg3 16. fxg3
O-O-O $15) 10... Qa5+ 11. Qd2 Qxd2+ 12. Nxd2 {Black has a slight space
advantage. Such endings are won by the player who plays better.} h6 13. Bh4 g6
14. Bxd7+ Nxd7 15. dxe5 Bxe5 16. O-O-O O-O 17. c4 Nb6 18. cxd5 Nxd5 19. Nc4
Rfe8 20. Bg3 Bxg3 21. hxg3 Kg7 22. Rd4 Re7 23. Rhd1 Rae8 24. e4 Nf6 25. f3 Rc8
26. g4 Rcc7 27. Rd8 b6 28. Nd6 Kh7 29. Nc4 Kg7 30. Ra8 Rcd7 31. Nd6 Re6 32. Nc4
Rxd1+ 33. Kxd1 Re7 34. b4 h5 35. gxh5 Nxh5 36. Rc8 Nf4 37. Rxc6 Nxg2 38. a4
Rd7+ 39. Nd6 Kf6 40. Ke2 Ke5 41. Nc4+ Kd4 42. b5 Nf4+ 43. Kd2 Ne6 44. Rd6+ Rxd6
45. Nxd6 f6 46. Nc8 Nc5 47. Nxa7 Nxa4 1/2-1/2

