{Another game showing typical strategies in the Colle system coming from a
different move order!} 1. Nf3 d5 2. b3 Nf6 3. Bb2 e6 4. e3 Be7 5. c4 b6 6. d4
O-O 7. Nbd2 Bb7 8. Bd3 dxc4 $1 9. bxc4 (9. Nxc4 Nbd7 10. O-O c5 $11 {leads to
a symmetrical pawn structure.}) 9... c5 10. Qe2 (10. O-O cxd4 11. exd4 Nc6 12.
Ne5 (12. Qe2 Re8 (12... Nb4 13. Bb1 Re8 14. a3 Nc6 15. Bd3 Bf8 16. Rfe1 g6 17.
Rad1 Bg7 18. Nf1 Rc8 (18... Nh5) (18... Nh5 19. Bb1 Rc8)) 13. Qe3 Rc8 14. Ne5
Nxe5 (14... Bf8 15. f4)) 12... Nxd4) (10. Ne5 cxd4 11. exd4 Re8 12. O-O Nc6 13.
Ndf3 Nxe5 14. Nxe5) 10... Re8 11. O-O cxd4 12. exd4 Bf8 $1 13. Rad1 {I believe
that this is the right setup for White - putting the rooks on d1 and e1 and
play in the center and on the kingside.} Nc6 $1 (13... Nbd7 $6 {The knight on
d7 is good for defence, but it does not put any pressure on the hanging pawns!
cannot be called a mistake, but the knight is very passive there.}) 14. Bb1 g6
{Black has a satisfactory game.} 15. Ne4 {This helps Black - exchanges are
favorable for the side playing against the hanging pawns.} (15. Ne5 $2 Nxd4 $2
(15... Rc8) (15... Bg7) 16. Bxd4 (16. Qe1 $3 {[%csl Gb2,Gd1,Rd4][%cal Yd1d8,
Yd2b3]}) 16... Qxd4 $19) (15. Qe3 $5 Bg7 {Now Black wants to play ...Rc8 and
then ...Na5 or ...Ne7.} 16. Ne5 $5 Nxe5 $2 ({We can ignore the knight with} 
16... Ne7 17. f4) 17. dxe5 Nd7 18. Be4 $1 $16 {Ultimately White's knight will
come to e4, where it poses a lot of problems for Black.} (18. Ne4 $2 Bxe4 $1
19. Bxe4 Rc8 $15 {Now Black has a good position. For example} 20. f4 Qc7 21.
Bd3 Nc5 22. Be2 Red8 23. h3 Rxd1 (23... Qc6 {[%cal Yc6a4]}) (23... Bf8 {
[%cal Yf8c5]}) 24. Rxd1 Rd8) 18... Nc5 19. Bxb7 Nxb7 20. Ne4 $16 {[%csl Ge4]})
15... Nxe4 16. Bxe4 Bg7 17. Ne5 (17. Bb1 Qc7 $15) 17... Qc7 18. f4 {White
strengthens the position of the knight on e5, but long-term it creates huge
weaknesses.} (18. Nxc6 Bxc6 19. Bxc6 Qxc6 20. Rc1 Rac8 21. Rfd1 Qa4 22. Ba1
Red8 $15) 18... Nxe5 19. Bxb7 $6 (19. fxe5 Bxe4 20. Qxe4 Qxc4 21. Qf4 Qc7 22.
Ba3 Rac8 23. Bd6 Qb7 $17) (19. dxe5 Bxe4 20. Qxe4 Rac8 $17) 19... Qxc4 $1 $17
20. Ba6 (20. Qxc4 Nxc4 21. Bxa8 Nxb2 22. Bc6 (22. Rd2 Rxa8 $19) 22... Rc8 23.
Rc1 Bxd4+ 24. Kh1 Nd3 $17) 20... Qxe2 21. Bxe2 Nc6 22. Bb5 Rac8 $17 23. d5 exd5
24. Bxg7 Kxg7 25. Rc1 Nd4 26. Bxe8 Ne2+ 27. Kf2 Nxc1 28. Ba4 Rc4 0-1

