{A great Blitz game by the two World Champions! Demonstrating typical ideas in
the Colle System with parallel hanging pawns in the center!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6
3. Nf3 b6 4. e3 Bb7 5. Bd3 d5 6. b3 c5 7. O-O cxd4 8. exd4 Be7 9. Nbd2 O-O 10.
Bb2 Nc6 $1 {The knight belongs to c6 in these positions. From there it can
attack the d4- as well as the c4 pawn! On d7 this knght would have been very
passive!} 11. Qe2 Re8 12. Rad1 Bf8 $1 (12... dxc4 13. bxc4 Na5 14. Nb3 $1) 13.
Rfe1 g6 $1 {This is the plan - preparing ...Bf8, ...g6, ...Bg7, and ...dc4 at
a good moment!} 14. Bb1 Bg7 15. Ne5 (15. Qe3 Rc8 16. Ne5 dxc4 (16... Ne7) 17.
bxc4 Ne7) (15. c5 $2 bxc5 (15... Nd7 {would be another typical idea - White is
not ready to support the c5-pawn with b4.} 16. cxb6 Qxb6 $15 17. Nf1 {How
should Black continue?} {Both} a5 {, starting a mini minority attack and} (
17... Ba6 {are very interesting.})) 16. dxc5 Qa5 $17 {[%csl Rc5]} (16... e5))
15... Rc8 (15... dxc4 $5 16. bxc4 (16. Nxc6 Bxc6 17. bxc4 Rc8 $15) 16... Nxd4
$15 (16... Nxe5 $2 17. dxe5 Nd7 18. Be4 $1 (18. Ne4 Bxe4 19. Bxe4 Rc8) 18...
Qc7 19. Bxb7 Qxb7 20. Ne4 $16)) 16. Ndf3 Nd7 17. Ng4 (17. Nxd7 Qxd7 18. c5 $2
bxc5 19. dxc5 e5 $15) 17... h5 18. Ne3 Ne7 19. h3 Nf6 20. Ne5 Nf5 21. Nf1 Nd6
22. Ne3 Nf5 23. Nf1 Ne4 24. Bxe4 dxe4 25. Ne3 Qc7 26. Nxf5 exf5 27. Bc1 Qe7 28.
Qe3 Qd8 29. Qg3 h4 30. Qf4 Re6 31. c5 b5 32. a4 bxa4 33. Nc4 axb3 34. Nd6 Bd5
35. Nxc8 Qxc8 36. Qxh4 a5 37. Bb2 a4 38. Ra1 Ra6 39. Qf4 Bf6 40. Ra3 Kg7 41.
Rea1 Qc6 42. Qb8 e3 43. f3 Qe6 44. Qb5 e2 45. Re1 Qe3+ 46. Kh2 Re6 47. Qxa4 Bh4
48. Qb4 Qf2 49. Raa1 Bg3+ 50. Kh1 Bxf3 51. d5+ Kh7 52. Rg1 Re4 53. Qb7 Bxg2+
54. Rxg2 e1=Q+ 55. Rg1 Qf3# 0-1

