1. d4 Nf6 2. e3 e6 3. Nf3 c5 4. Be2 b6 5. O-O Bb7 6. Nbd2 Be7 7. b3 O-O 8. Bb2
cxd4 9. exd4 Nc6 10. c4 d5 11. a3 Rc8 12. Rc1 dxc4 (12... Re8 13. c5 a5 $1 {
[%cal Yf6d7]} (13... Nd7 $6 14. b4 $1)) 13. bxc4 Qd6 {This was a blitz game of
mine - I didn't know the correct plan with ...Re8 in 2009. But ...Qd6 also
makes sense.} (13... Re8 {[%cal Ye7f8,Yg7g6,Yf8g7]}) 14. h3 Rfd8 15. Qb3 Na5
16. Qa2 {How to continue with Black here?} Ne4 $1 {It's favourable for Black
to exchange minor pieces. Also, now we can put our bishop on f6.} 17. Nxe4 Bxe4
18. Rfd1 Qf4 19. g3 Qh6 20. Kh2 Bf6 21. Ne5 Bxe5 22. dxe5 Rd2 {[%csl Rb2,Re2]}
23. Rxd2 Qxd2 $19 24. Bc3 $4 Qxa2 0-1

