1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. Nbd2 d5 6. O-O g6 7. b3 Bg7 8. Bb2 (
8. Ba3 Nbd7 {[%cal Yc7c5,Ye8g8]}) 8... O-O 9. Qe2 c5 10. Ne5 (10. dxc5 bxc5 {
Possible this is the correct move - White can give us hanging pawns.} 11. c4
Nbd7 12. cxd5 exd5 $13) (10. c4 dxc4 11. bxc4 cxd4 12. exd4 Nc6 {We have won
two tempi compared to positions where we started with ...Be7 - this counts for
something!}) 10... Nbd7 11. f4 {This play is not strategically justified here
since Black has a very solid position on the kingside.} Rc8 12. Rac1 Ne4 13.
Bxe4 dxe4 14. c4 f5 $15 {Black intends to later take on e5. White's problem is
the passive knight on d2.} 15. Nxd7 Qxd7 16. Rfd1 cxd4 17. exd4 Bxd4+ 18. Bxd4
Qxd4+ 19. Kh1 Qd3 20. Qxd3 exd3 21. Nf3 Bxf3 22. gxf3 Rfd8 23. Rd2 Rd4 24. Re1
Kf7 25. Kg2 Rcd8 26. Red1 Kf6 27. Kf2 Rxf4 28. Rxd3 Rxd3 29. Rxd3 Ke7 30. Ke3
Rh4 31. Rd2 g5 32. b4 Rxc4 33. Rd3 Rxb4 0-1

