1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. c4 e6 4. e3 a6 5. b3 c5 6. Nbd2 Nc6 7. Bb2 cxd4 8. exd4
Be7 9. Bd3 O-O 10. O-O b6 11. Rc1 Bb7 {By a different move order we have
reached a typical position. Black would rather have his pawn on a7 instead of
a6 as now b6 can be weak.} 12. Re1 (12. c5 $2 Nd7 (12... bxc5 13. dxc5 Nd7) 13.
cxb6 Qxb6) 12... dxc4 13. bxc4 Rc8 14. Qe2 Re8 15. a3 Bf8 16. Bb1 g6 17. Ne4
Bg7 18. Neg5 (18. h3 Nd7 19. Ne5 Ncxe5 20. dxe5 Bxe4 $3 21. Bxe4 Nc5 22. Bc2)
18... Na5 $2 {Giving up control over the e5-square.} 19. Ne5 $16 Rc7 20. h4 Nc6
21. Rcd1 Nxe5 22. dxe5 Nd7 23. Qe3 (23. Ne4 Bxe4 $3 24. Bxe4 Qe7 25. g3 Nc5 26.
Bc2 Rd8 $11) 23... Qa8 (23... Qe7 $142 $13) 24. Qf4 Nc5 25. f3 Rd8 26. h5 Rcd7
27. Rxd7 Rxd7 28. Nxh7 Kxh7 29. hxg6+ fxg6 30. Qh4+ Bh6 31. Qh5 Nd3 32. Qg4 Qe8
33. Rd1 Be3+ 34. Kf1 Nxe5 35. Rxd7+ Qxd7 36. Bxg6+ Nxg6 37. Qh5+ Bh6 38. f4
Qd3+ 39. Kg1 Qe3+ 40. Kh2 Qxf4+ 0-1

