1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. b3 (6. c4 $1 Bg7 7. Nc3
O-O 8. e4 d6) 6... Bg7 7. Bb2 O-O 8. Nbd2 {Against this setup by White our
plan with ...g6 works perfectly!} d5 (8... c5) 9. c4 Nbd7 10. Qc2 {The queen
does not belong to c2 in the Colle System. We punish non-standard moves by
making standard moves!} c5 ({or} 10... dxc4 11. bxc4 (11. Bxc4 c5) ({If White
takes with the knight} 11. Nxc4 {we will seriously consider} Bxf3 12. gxf3 c5)
11... c5) 11. Rad1 Rc8 {[%cal Yc8c2]} 12. Qb1 Qe7 (12... cxd4 13. exd4 Nh5 $5 {
Black wants to play ...Nf4 and would be very happy to see a move like} 14. g3 {
when White has created weaknesses.} dxc4 15. bxc4 Re8 {Our only bad piece is
the knight on d7 - we may even consider rerouting to c6 via b8.}) 13. Rfe1 cxd4
14. exd4 Rfd8 15. Qc1 dxc4 16. bxc4 Nh5 17. Ne4 Ndf6 {Black tries to exchange
pieces, which is favourable to him.} 18. Ba3 Qc7 19. Nxf6+ Bxf6 $17 {Suddenly
White cannot keep his position together.} 20. Be2 (20. Be4 Bxe4 21. Rxe4 Qxc4)
20... Nf4 21. Qe3 Nxe2+ 22. Qxe2 Qxc4 23. Qe3 Qxa2 24. Ra1 Qd5 25. Bb2 a5 26.
Rab1 b5 27. Ba1 b4 28. Bb2 Rc4 29. Ba1 a4 30. Qd2 b3 31. Qe3 Rc2 32. Bb2 Rdc8
33. Ba3 R8c3 34. Qe2 0-1

