1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. b3 Bg7 7. Bb2 O-O 8. c4 d6
(8... d5 {If White takes on d5} 9. cxd5 {then} Nxd5 $1 {is the correct move.
We have some kind of Grunfeld Defence, with very good play for Black. For
example} (9... exd5 10. b4 Nbd7 11. Nc3 Ne4 12. b5 {[%csl Rb7,Rg7]}) 10. Nc3
Nxc3 11. Bxc3 c5 12. Qe2 Nd7 13. Rad1 {How to continue now?} Bxf3 $1 14. Qxf3
cxd4 {White will be left with an isolated d-pawn.}) 9. Nbd2 Nbd7 10. Qc2 Re8 (
10... c5 {is another flexible and good setup.}) 11. Ne4 Qe7 12. Rad1 Rac8 13.
Nfd2 Nxe4 14. Nxe4 d5 15. Nd2 c5 16. dxc5 Bxb2 17. Qxb2 Nxc5 18. Bb1 e5 ({
Another option would have been} 18... dxc4 19. Nxc4 Ba6 {to exchange on c4 and
leave White with a powerless bishop on b1.}) 19. cxd5 Bxd5 20. e4 Bb7 {[%csl
Rb1] White is left with a bad bishop on b1, Black is clearly better.} 21. f3
Qg5 22. Nc4 Ba6 23. Rc1 Bxc4 24. Rxc4 Ne6 25. Rfc1 Rxc4 26. Rxc4 Nf4 27. Kf1
Rd8 28. Qc2 Qh4 29. g3 Qh3+ 30. Kg1 Rd1+ 0-1

