1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. c4 Bg7 7. Nc3 O-O 8. e4 d6
9. Qe2 Nbd7 ({or} 9... Nc6) 10. e5 $2 {A tactical mistake.} dxe5 (10... Bxf3 $1
11. gxf3 (11. Qxf3 dxe5 $17) 11... dxe5 (11... Nh5 12. f4 c5 $1 {would also be
good - destroying White's center.}) 12. dxe5 Nxe5 $1 $19 {[%csl Rd3]}) 11. Nxe5
c5 12. Nxd7 Qxd7 13. dxc5 Qc6 $1 14. f3 Qxc5+ 15. Be3 Qe5 $5 {Centralizing the
queen - here the queen is annoying for White. If White kicks it away with f4,
he creates weaknesses.} 16. Rac1 Rad8 17. Bb1 Nh5 18. g3 Rfe8 19. Qf2 Qb8 {
Finally I went back with my queen, but only after White has weakened his
position with g3.} 20. Be4 Nf6 21. Bxb7 Qxb7 {I have a playable position -
nothing tremendous - and won the game in the end.} 22. Bg5 h6 23. Be3 Rd3 24.
Qe2 Red8 25. Nd5 R3xd5 26. cxd5 Nxd5 {I allowed him to win an exchange, though
I would evaluate the position as unclear - with chances for both sides.} 27.
Rfd1 h5 {I would prefer to play Black in a standard game as he has the
initiative.} 28. Bd4 Nf4 29. gxf4 Bxd4+ 30. Kg2 Rd5 31. Rd3 Bf6 32. Rxd5 Qxd5
33. b3 Qd4 34. Rd1 Qxf4 35. Qe4 Qg5+ 36. Kh1 Kg7 37. Rd7 Qb5 38. Qd3 Qa5 39. a4
Qe1+ 40. Kg2 a5 41. Qe4 Qc3 42. Qxe6 Qb2+ 43. Kh3 Kh6 44. Qxf7 Qe5 45. Qh7+ Kg5
0-1

