1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. c4 Bg7 7. Nc3 O-O 8. e4 d6
9. Bg5 h6 10. Bd2 c5 11. d5 e5 {White has a clear advantage according to the
computer, but this is not so clear in practice.} 12. a3 Nh5 {Black has a clear
plan - to prepare ...f5.} 13. Qc1 Kh7 14. Ne1 Nd7 15. Be2 Nhf6 16. Nd3 Ba6 17.
b3 Ne8 18. Ra2 Qe7 19. Qc2 Nc7 20. a4 f5 21. f3 f4 {Typical King's Indian
strategy.} 22. Nb5 Nf6 23. b4 (23. Nxc7 Qxc7 24. Kh1 Bc8 {If Black where to
move again, for example after} 25. Bc3 {, then he would close the queenside
with} a5 $1 {and as a consequence, have a free hand on the kingside.}) 23... g5
24. bxc5 bxc5 25. Bc3 Ng8 26. Rd1 Ne8 27. Rb2 h5 28. Rdb1 Nh6 29. Na3 Nf6 30.
Nb5 Nf7 31. Ba5 Rac8 32. Ne1 g4 33. Rb3 Bh6 34. R1b2 Rg8 35. Kh1 Rg7 36. Qb1
Bg5 37. Na3 Bh4 38. Rb8 Ng5 39. Rxc8 Bxc8 40. Rb8 Qd7 41. Nb5 Bxe1 42. Qxe1
gxf3 43. gxf3 (43. gxf3 Qh3 $19) 0-1

