1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. c4 Bg7 7. b3 O-O 8. Bb2 {
The setup with b3-Bb2 is not successful against our setup with g6-Bg7. Now we
can choose between three good moves:} d6 $5 (8... d5 {and if White takes on d5}
9. cxd5 {we play} Nxd5 $1 (9... exd5 10. Nc3 $14)) (8... c5 9. Nbd2 cxd4 10.
exd4 ({White can play} 10. Nxd4 {with an equal position.} Nc6) 10... d5 11. Rc1
dxc4 12. bxc4 Nc6) 9. Nc3 Nbd7 10. Qe2 e5 11. d5 Nh5 $3 {Look at this clever
move! White cannot stop ...f5 and e4 is met by ...Nf4.} 12. b4 f5 13. Bc2 Qe7
14. Ba4 e4 15. Nd4 Bxd4 16. exd4 Nf4 17. Qe3 Nd3 18. Ba3 a5 $1 19. bxa5 $6 Rxa5
$17 20. f3 Nf6 21. Rab1 Ba6 22. fxe4 fxe4 23. Bb4 Rxa4 24. Nxa4 Bxc4 25. Nc3
Nxb4 0-1

