1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. a4 {This is also playable,
as is} (6. Qe2 {when we have three possible moves:} d5 (6... c5) (6... Bg7))
6... a5 7. b3 Bg7 8. Ba3 d6 9. c4 O-O 10. Nc3 Nbd7 {We got an unclear position
out of the opening, where Black can play for a win.} 11. Rc1 Re8 12. e4 e5 13.
d5 {Black is better here - b3-a4 looks bad.} Nh5 (13... Bh6 {is possibly even
better.}) 14. b4 axb4 15. Bxb4 Bh6 16. Ra1 Nf4 17. g3 Nxd3 18. Qxd3 Rf8 {
Black prepares ...f5 and has a good game. The b7-bishop will join the action
via c8.} 19. Nh4 Bg5 20. Ng2 f5 21. f3 f4 22. g4 h5 23. h3 hxg4 24. hxg4 Kg7
