1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. e3 b6 4. Bd3 Bb7 5. O-O g6 6. b3 Bg7 7. Bb2 O-O 8. Nbd2
d6 ({Or} 8... c5 9. c4 Nc6 (9... cxd4 10. exd4 d5) 10. Rc1 Nh5 $3 {A rare and
good idea - Black wants to play either ...cxd4, followed by ...Nf4, or play ...
f5.} 11. Re1 f5 $3 12. Bb1 Qe7 (12... g5)) 9. Qe2 (9. e4 c5 10. dxc5 bxc5) 9...
c5 10. Rfd1 Nc6 $1 ({According to the computer, Black is better after} 10...
cxd4 $3 11. exd4 Nd5 $1 12. g3 Nb4 {, collecting White's light-squared bishop.}
) 11. a3 Qe7 12. Ba6 ({If} 12. c4 {then} cxd4 ({or} 12... Nh5 $5 13. Bc2 f5 14.
Rab1 g5 {[%cal Yg5g4]}) 13. exd4 d5 14. Rac1 dxc4 15. bxc4 Rfd8 16. Nb3 Rac8)
12... Rad8 13. Bxb7 Qxb7 14. Rab1 (14. c4 cxd4 (14... Nh5) 15. exd4 d5 16. c5
$6 Nd7 $1 17. cxb6 (17. b4 bxc5 $19) 17... Qxb6 $15) 14... Nh5 15. dxc5 Bxb2 {
Black exchanges on b2 since the rook is worse on b2 than on b1.} 16. Rxb2 dxc5
17. Rbb1 Nf6 18. Qc4 Nd5 {The position is about equal but not a draw.} 19. Ra1
Qe7 20. Ne4 Rd7 21. b4 Rfd8 22. bxc5 $2 Nxe3 $1 23. Rxd7 Nxc4 24. Rxe7 Nxe7 25.
cxb6 axb6 $17 {Now Black has a clear positional advantage in the endgame.} 26.
g3 Nc6 27. Kg2 f5 28. Nc3 e5 29. a4 e4 30. Ng1 Rd2 31. Nge2 Rxc2 32. Rd1 N6e5
33. Rd8+ Kg7 34. Rb8 g5 35. Rb7+ Kh6 36. Kf1 f4 37. gxf4 gxf4 38. Nxf4 Rxc3 39.
Nd5 Rf3 40. Kg2 Nd3 41. Nxb6 Rxf2+ 42. Kg3 Rf3+ 43. Kh4 Ne3 0-1

