1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 e6 3. e3 c5 4. c3 cxd4 $1 5. exd4 Be7 6. h3 d6 (6... O-O {
is also possible. Just to mention a typical mistake:} {if White plays} 7. Bc4 {
we DON'T play} d5 $2 8. Bd3 Nc6 9. Nf3 $14) 7. Nf3 (7. Bb5+ {Against
non-standard moves, we play STANDARD moves!} Nbd7 $1 (7... Bd7 $6 8. Bd3)) 7...
Nbd7 (7... b6 {is also possible, when we can again answer} 8. Bb5+ {with} Nbd7
9. Bc6 {leads to nothing after} Rb8) 8. Qe2 $2 b6 9. Nbd2 Bb7 (9... a5 {
ist this the way to punish 8.Qe2?} {No! White just plays} 10. Qd1 {and ...a5
has created a permanent weakness.}) 10. Qe3 $2 O-O {We ignore the mistakes
made by White for now and want to focus on the ideas in the middle game.} ({
Black could have won by} 10... Nd5 {but it is just a blitz game.} 11. Qe4 N7f6
12. Bb5+ Kf8 13. Qc2 Nxf4 $19) 11. Bd3 Re8 12. O-O Bf8 (12... Nd5 13. Qe4 N7f6
$19) (12... a6) 13. Bg5 a6 14. Rfe1 (14. Ne4 Be7 $1 15. Nxf6+ Nxf6 $11 (15...
Bxf6 $11)) 14... Qc7 {We have reached a typical position. Black has arranged
her pieces in a good way and has an equal game.} 15. Bxf6 (15. a4 Bc6 16. Qe2 (
16. c4 d5) 16... Qb7 17. Bc2 b5) 15... Nxf6 {Now Black has a great game. Later
she won the game with a minority attack.} 16. Qg5 (16. a4 Bc6 $1 17. Qe2 Qb7
18. c4 d5) 16... Bc6 17. Ne4 Nxe4 18. Bxe4 Bxe4 19. Rxe4 Be7 20. Qg3 b5 21.
Rae1 (21. Rg4 Bf8 (21... g6 22. h4 Rac8 23. h5 Bf6 24. hxg6 hxg6 $15) 22. h4 b4
$1 23. cxb4 Qc2 $17 {Black is way ahead with his attack.}) 21... Rac8 22. a3 d5
$1 23. Qxc7 Rxc7 $15 {After exchanging queens, Black can carry out her
minority attack in the endgame. White no longer has chances for counterplay on
the kingside.} 24. R4e2 (24. Re5 Rb8 {[%cal Ya6a5,Yb5b4]} (24... Bd6 $4 25.
Rxd5 $16)) 24... a5 (24... Bd6 25. Ne5 Bxe5 26. Rxe5 (26. dxe5 Rc4 $17 27. g3
g5 28. Kg2 a5 29. Rd2 Rec8 30. Ree2 Kg7 31. f3 Kg6 32. Kf2 b4 33. cxb4 axb4 34.
axb4 Rxb4 $19) 26... Rb8 (26... a5 $4 27. Rxd5) 27. R5e3 a5 28. Kf1 b4 29. axb4
axb4 $15 30. cxb4 (30. Rd1 bxc3 31. Rxc3 Rcb7 {[%csl Rb2,Rd4]}) 30... Rxb4 {
[%csl Rb2,Rd4]}) 25. Ne5 (25. Rc1 Rb7 26. Ree1 Rc8 $1 (26... b4 27. axb4 axb4
28. c4 $1 dxc4 29. Rxc4 $11)) 25... b4 26. axb4 (26. cxb4 axb4 27. a4 b3 {
[%csl Rd4]} 28. Re3 Ra7 (28... Rb7) 29. Rxb3 Rxa4 30. Nf3 Bf6 31. Rd1 g6 32.
Rbd3 Rb4 33. b3 Reb8 34. Rb1 Rc8 35. Rb2 Kg7 36. g3 g5 $17) 26... axb4 27. cxb4
Bxb4 28. Rd1 Bd6 29. Nd3 (29. g3 Bxe5 $1 30. dxe5 Rb8 31. Kg2 Rcb7 32. Rdd2 g5
$1 (32... h5 $6 33. h4 g6 34. f3 Kg7 35. f4 $15) 33. Rc2 Kg7 34. Red2 Kg6 $17)
29... Rb8 30. f4 g6 31. Kf2 Rb3 32. g3 Rc4 33. Ne5 Bxe5 34. fxe5 Rcb4 35. Rdd2
g5 $1 (35... h5 36. h4) 36. Kg2 h5 37. Rf2 Kg7 38. g4 hxg4 $2 (38... h4 $1 39.
Rfe2 Rg3+ 40. Kh2 Rbb3 $19) 39. hxg4 Ra4 40. Rf3 Rbb4 41. Rfd3 Ra2 42. b3 Rxb3
43. Rxa2 Rxd3 44. Ra4 Kg6 45. Kf2 Rc3 46. Ke2 Rg3 47. Ra8 Rxg4 48. Ke3 Re4+ 49.
Kd3 g4 50. Rf8 Kg7 51. Ra8 g3 52. Ra2 Rg4 53. Rg2 Kg6 54. Ke3 Kf5 55. Kf3 Rxd4
56. Rxg3 Rd3+ 57. Kf2 Rxg3 58. Kxg3 Kxe5 0-1

