1. d4 Nf6 2. Bf4 e6 3. e3 c5 4. c3 cxd4 5. exd4 d6 6. Nd2 Be7 7. Ngf3 O-O 8.
Bd3 b6 9. O-O {Plans with long castling are possible, but very risky:} (9. Qc2
Bb7 10. O-O-O Nbd7 11. g4 Rc8 {I believe that we can sacrifice the h7-pawn.} (
11... g6) (11... Kh8) 12. g5 Nd5 13. Bxh7+ Kh8 14. Bg3 Nb4 15. Qb1 Nxa2+ 16.
Qxa2 Kxh7 $17) (9. Qe2 Bb7 10. O-O-O Nbd7 11. h4 b5 $5 {Not necessary but
interesting!} 12. Bxb5 Rb8 $44 {[%cal Yd8a5,Yf8c8]}) ({Can White start
attacking with h2-h4? This would be possible with a black pawn on d5 instead
of d6. Here, Black can prepare a counterplay in the center with ...e6-e5. For
example} 9. h4 Bb7 10. Kf1 Nbd7 11. Rg1 Re8 12. g4 {This is like an attack of
an angy person - it leads to nothing good.} e5 $1 $19 {Played according to
basic chess principles: an attack on the wing is answered by counterplay in
the center!} 13. dxe5 dxe5 14. Bxe5 Nxe5 15. Nxe5 Bd6 16. Nef3 (16. Nec4 Bh2)
16... Bh2 17. Nxh2 Qxd3+) 9... Bb7 10. Re1 Nbd7 11. Qe2 a6 (11... Nd5 $3 12.
Bg3 N7f6 {This is rarely working but here it appears to be good.} 13. h3 Nh5)
12. a4 Re8 13. Bc4 Bf8 ({Not} 13... d5 $2 14. Bd3 $16) (13... Nf8 $5 {is
another good defensive move.}) 14. Bg5 (14. Ng5 Qe7 (14... Nd5 $4 15. Qh5 $18))
14... h6 15. Bh4 Qc8 16. Ba2 Bc6 $15 17. a5 $2 b5 $17 ({It was even better to
accept the pawn.} 17... bxa5 $3 18. Bb3 Qc7 $19) 18. Rac1 Qb7 19. b3 e5 20.
dxe5 Nxe5 21. Bxf6 Nxf3+ 22. Qxf3 Bxf3 23. Nxf3 gxf6 0-1

