{You can find the last moves of this game on YouTube and watch the two players
move their pieces fast! This game is a good example of how White should play:
manoeuvre "up and down" with the pieces, avoid exchanges, and wait for a good
moment to attack! Black had a great position after the opening, but later he
went wrong and ended up with a lost position. Still, he managed to complicate
matters (it was a blitz game) and win in the end!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5
c5 4. e3 cxd4 5. exd4 (5. Nxd4 $4 Qa5+ $19) 5... Be7 {We use exactly the same
setup as against the London System!} 6. Bd3 b6 7. Qe2 Bb7 8. Nbd2 a6 9. c3 d6
10. O-O Nbd7 11. a4 O-O {White has one basic plan: he must manoeuvre with his
pieces and keep the tension, hoping to find a good moment to start an attack.
For Black, it's the same, and he can also prepare ...b5.} 12. Rfe1 Re8 {
A multipurpose move: it is useful to protect the bishop (...Qc7 might allow
Ne4), ...e5 is prepared, and f8 is vacated for the bishop or the knight.} 13.
Bh4 Qc8 {Intending to play ...Bc6 (without blundering the a6-pawn).} (13... Nf8
$5 14. h3 Ng6 15. Bg3 Nh5 $132) 14. Ng5 Bf8 (14... Qc6 $1) 15. Nc4 ({I want to
point out a motif and enter a random move for White:} 15. Qd1 Bc6 16. Qc2 {
How to protect h7? With ...g6 or ...h6?} g6 {is of course the answer, with a
totally acceptable game.} (16... h6 $4 17. Bh7+ Kh8 18. Nxf7#)) 15... g6 16.
Bg3 Qc6 17. Ne3 Qc7 $132 18. h3 Bh6 19. Bh4 Bg7 20. Ng4 $2 Nh5 (20... h6 $1 21.
Nf3 (21. Nxf6+ $4 Bxf6 22. Nf3 Bxf3 23. Qxf3 Bxh4 $19) 21... Nh5 22. Bc2 e5 $15
) (20... e5 $1 $15 21. Nxf6+ Bxf6) 21. Qd2 Qc6 22. Be4 Qc7 23. Bxb7 Qxb7 24.
Ne4 $1 Qc7 25. Nh6+ $3 $16 Kf8 26. c4 Ndf6 27. Nc3 Ng8 28. Nxg8 Kxg8 29. b3
Rac8 30. Rac1 Qd7 31. g4 Nf6 32. Qf4 e5 33. dxe5 dxe5 34. Qe3 Qe6 35. Bxf6 Bxf6
36. Nd5 Bd8 37. Rcd1 e4 38. Qd4 Rb8 39. f3 Qd6 40. Kg2 exf3+ 41. Kxf3 Qc6 42.
Re4 Bh4 43. Rxe8+ Qxe8 44. Qf4 h6 45. Qxh6 Bd8 46. Qf4 Rb7 47. Qe4 Qf8 48. Nf6+
Bxf6 49. Qxb7 Qc5 50. Qe4 Kg7 51. Kg2 Qa3 52. Qc2 Qc5 53. Qf2 Qe5 54. Rf1 a5
55. Qxb6 Qe4+ 56. Rf3 Bd4 57. Qc7 Qe2+ 58. Kg3 Be5+ 59. Qxe5+ Qxe5+ 60. Kg2 Qe4
61. Kg3 f5 62. gxf5 gxf5 63. Rf4 Qe5 64. Kf3 Kf6 65. h4 Qc3+ 66. Kf2 Qc2+ 67.
Kg1 Qc1+ 68. Rf1 Qe3+ 69. Rf2 Qg3+ 70. Kf1 f4 71. h5 f3 72. h6 Kg6 73. c5 Kxh6
74. c6 Qh3+ 75. Kg1 Qg3+ 76. Kf1 Qf4 77. Rc2 Qe4 78. Rh2+ Kg5 79. c7 Qd3+ 80.
Kf2 Qe2+ 81. Kg3 Qe5+ 0-1

