{A great game by Black!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 c5 4. e3 cxd4 5. exd4 b6 6.
Bd3 Bb7 7. Nbd2 Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. Qe2 (9. c4 d5 {The typical reaction after c4
is to play ...d5 - Black gets a good version of an IQP position. For example}
10. Re1 dxc4 11. Nxc4 Nc6 12. Nce5 Nxe5 ({or} 12... Nb4 13. Bb1 Nbd5 $11) 13.
dxe5 Nd5 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 $15) ({If} 9. c3 {we play} d6 {and keep the diagonal
open for our b7-bishop.}) 9... d6 10. Rfe1 a6 {This is not necessary yet, but
anyway belongs to Black's setup.} ({or} 10... Nbd7 {when} 11. Ba6 Bxa6 12. Qxa6
Qc8 {is not a threat - exchanges favour Black.}) 11. Nf1 Nbd7 12. Ng3 Re8 13.
a3 Qc8 ({or} 13... Qc7 14. Rad1 b5) (13... b5 {also was possible since a4 can
be met with ...b4.}) 14. Nd2 Bf8 15. Qf1 Bc6 16. Nde4 Nxe4 (16... Be7 {was
also acceptable and maybe better than taking on e4.} 17. Bxf6 Nxf6 $11) 17.
Nxe4 Qb7 18. c3 b5 {Black has a good game, the only thing that annoys me a
little is that Black's pieces cannot use the f6-square.} 19. f3 Rac8 20. Rad1
Bd5 (20... Qb8 $5 {protecting d6 and preparing ...Be7.}) 21. Nd2 (21. h3 Bc4
22. Bxc4 Rxc4 (22... bxc4 23. Bc1) 23. Nd2 Rcc8 (23... Rc6 24. d5 Rcc8 25. dxe6
fxe6) 24. d5 e5 (24... Qxd5)) 21... Qb6 22. Kh1 g6 23. Qf2 Bg7 24. Qh4 Bb7 {
Black has two active plans: either he will go for ...a5 and ...b4, or he will
go for ...e5.} 25. Be4 (25. Ne4 a5 ({I don't like} 25... d5 $2 26. Nf6+ Nxf6
27. Bxf6 a5 28. Bxg7 Kxg7 29. Qf4 {with attacking chances for White.}) ({or} 
25... Bxe4 $2 26. fxe4 $16)) 25... a5 (25... d5 26. Bd3 a5 $15) 26. Bxb7 Qxb7
27. Ne4 Qb6 28. Bd2 (28. d5 e5 29. Be7 $2 Rc4 $1 30. b3 $2 Rxe4 $1 31. fxe4 f6
$17 {[%csl Re7]}) (28. Nf6+ Nxf6 29. Bxf6 Bxf6 30. Qxf6 Qd8 (30... b4 $15) 31.
Qxd8 Rexd8 32. Kg1 d5 33. Re2 Rc4 34. Kf2 b4 35. axb4 axb4 $15 36. cxb4 $2 Rxb4
$17 {[%csl Rb2,Rd4]}) 28... d5 29. Nf2 b4 $15 {Now Black is taking over.} 30.
axb4 axb4 31. Rb1 (31. Ra1) 31... b3 (31... bxc3 $15) 32. Ra1 Ra8 33. Nd3 Qb5
34. Nb4 Nb6 35. Qf2 Nc4 36. Qe2 Bf8 37. Qd3 (37. Rxa8 Rxa8 38. Nd3 (38. Qd3 Qb6
$19 {[%csl Rb2]}) 38... Nxb2 $1 39. Nxb2 Qxe2 40. Rxe2 Ra2 41. Nd3 Bh6 42. f4
Bxf4 43. Nxf4 b2 44. Re1 Ra1 $19) 37... Bxb4 38. cxb4 Ra2 39. Rxa2 bxa2 40. Bc3
