{In this blitz game, White lost his patience, pushed too hard against the
well-protected black king, and left his king weak! A very nice win for Black! 
(FOR ME WITH THE BLACK PIECES, IN FACT)} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 c5 4. e3
cxd4 5. exd4 Be7 6. Nbd2 d6 7. Bd3 a6 8. c3 b6 9. Qe2 Nbd7 10. O-O (10. O-O-O {
can be played, though it gives good counterplay to Black.} Bb7 $132 {[%cal
Yb6b5,Ya8c8,Yf6d5]}) (10. Kf1 $6 {is dubious - White does not manage to create
an attack. For example} Bb7 11. Re1 O-O 12. h4 Re8 13. h5 b5 {We are solid on
the kingside and can prepare active play in connection with a minority attack
or play in the center with ...e5. Long-term (if the position opens up),
White's king may feel very unsafe on f1.} 14. h6 g6) 10... Bb7 11. Rae1 (11.
Rfe1 O-O 12. Rad1 b5 13. h4 (13. a4 bxa4 14. Bc2 Nb6 15. Ra1 Bc6) 13... Re8 14.
Bf4 Bf8 (14... Qb6) 15. Ng5 Qc7 (15... g6 16. h5 Qc7 17. hxg6 hxg6) 16. h5 e5
17. dxe5 Nxe5 18. b3) 11... O-O 12. h3 Re8 {Black has a satisfactory game.} 13.
Nh2 (13. a4 Qc8 {[%cal Yb7c6]}) (13. c4 d5 {[%csl Rd4]}) (13. Ne4 Nxe4 14. Bxe7
Qxe7 15. Bxe4 Bxe4 16. Qxe4 Nf6 17. Qd3 b5 $132) 13... Qc7 (13... Nd5 $3 14.
Bxe7 Rxe7 15. f4 b5 $15) 14. f4 {There is not really an attack after this move,
which means that this is likely to backfire.} Bf8 (14... b5 $1) 15. Ng4 Nxg4
16. Qxg4 g6 17. Bh4 Bg7 18. Nf3 b5 $15 19. a3 Qb6 {I protect b5 to prepare ...
a5 and keep an eye on his king.} ({Should we play} 19... Nb6 {? No, the knight
is needed for defending the kingside - it should not move away.}) 20. Kh1 a5 {
Black is clearly better in my view.} 21. Ng5 Nf6 22. Qe2 b4 23. Bf2 Nd5 24. Qd2
bxa3 25. bxa3 Qc7 26. c4 Nf6 {I provoked c4 - White is overextended.} 27. Bh4
Rac8 28. Nf3 Nh5 29. Qe3 Ba8 {A clever little move, preparing ...Rb8-b3 and
maybe ...Qb7.} 30. g4 Nf6 31. Bg3 Rb8 32. c5 Nd5 33. Qf2 Rb3 34. Be4 Qd8 35. f5
dxc5 36. fxg6 hxg6 37. Ne5 f5 $1 {Black beats off White's attack.} 38. gxf5
gxf5 39. Bf3 cxd4 40. Qxd4 Rxf3 41. Rxf3 Nf6 42. Qe3 Nh5 43. Bh2 Qh4 44. Rg1
Kh7 45. Qe2 Bxe5 {Tiger Lilov resigns (Lag: Av=0.30s, max=0.6s)} 46. Bxe5 Qxh3+
0-1

