1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 h6 {This move has some advantages and disadvantages.
After inserting ...h6 Bh4 there are no more tricks with d4-d5, but on the
other hand ...h6 also may turn out as a weakening move.} 4. Bh4 c5 5. e3 cxd4
6. exd4 Be7 7. Nbd2 b6 8. c3 Bb7 9. Bd3 d6 10. O-O Nbd7 11. Re1 O-O 12. a4 a6
13. Qe2 Nh5 $1 {Now ...h6 turns out to be good. Black manages to exchange
bishops and ...Nf4 is threatened.} 14. Bxe7 Qxe7 15. Be4 Bxe4 16. Qxe4 Nhf6 17.
Qf4 b5 {Typical strategy.} 18. Ne4 Nxe4 19. Qxe4 Nf6 20. Qd3 Qb7 {Carlsen not
surprisingly knows all the typical ideas.} 21. axb5 axb5 22. Nd2 Ra4 23. b3
Rxa1 24. Rxa1 Ra8 25. Rxa8+ Qxa8 {Black is very slightly better, but the game
ended in a draw.} 26. Nf1 Nd5 27. g3 Qa5 28. c4 $11 bxc4 29. bxc4 Qc3 30. Qxc3
Nxc3 31. Kg2 Ne2 32. d5 exd5 33. cxd5 Nc3 34. Ne3 Kf8 35. Nf5 Nxd5 36. Nxd6
1/2-1/2

