1. d4 e6 (1... Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 c5 4. e3 cxd4 5. exd4 Be7 6. Nbd2 b6 7. c3
Bb7 8. Bxf6 Bxf6 9. Bd3 O-O 10. Qe2 d6 11. O-O-O Nd7 12. h4 Rc8 (12... a6 13.
g4 b5 14. Kb1 b4 15. c4) 13. Kb1) 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Bg5 c5 4. e3 Be7 5. Nbd2 cxd4
6. exd4 b6 7. c3 Bb7 8. Bd3 d6 9. Bxf6 $1 {Miladinovic's plan! White takes on
f6 before Black can connect his knights with ...Nbd7. I suggested this plan in
my proposed repertoire with the Torre Attack from White's point of view!} (9.
Qe2 Nbd7 10. Bxf6 $6 {Now this no longer makes sense as Black can recapture
with the knight.} Nxf6 $1) 9... Bxf6 10. Qe2 a6 ({Black should not castle
prematurely.} 10... O-O $2 11. O-O-O {is White's idea! This plan is effective
only in connection with Bxf6, as otherwise our knight could jump to d5 and
cause tactical problems for White. Now he gets dangerous attacking chances:}
Nd7 12. h4 a6 (12... Rc8 13. Kb1) 13. g4 b5 14. g5 $16 {White's attack
develops much faster than our counterplay.}) 11. h4 Nd7 12. a4 $5 {This is
interesting but very risky (typical Igor Miladinovic play)! Now White has a
problem with his king, as he cannot castle either way! His idea is to play Kf1
at some point, followed by Rh3-Rg3. We must not forget that by doing this, his
rooks are disconnected and they lose their potential! If Black can open the
center with a well-timed ...e6-e5, White may have a big problem!} (12. O-O-O {
was better in my opinion, for example} Be7 {(Black should play useful moves
preparing counterplay on the queenside and postpone castling)} 13. Kb1 Nf6 14.
g4 b5 15. g5 Nd5 $13 {[%cal Yd5f4,Ya8c8,Yc8c3]}) 12... Be7 13. Ne4 h6 (13...
Nf6 $1 {This appears to be simple enough: if we trade some pieces, we are free
to play ...0-0 and continue with the minority attack.} 14. Kf1 Nd5 $1 (14...
Nxe4 15. Bxe4 Bxe4 16. Qxe4 d5 17. Qd3 O-O 18. Ng5 $132)) ({We should avoid} 
13... d5 $2 14. Ned2 {[%csl Rb7]}) 14. Rh3 Qc7 15. Kf1 g6 $2 (15... O-O $132 {
was better than ...g6 - the position is very double-edged.}) (15... Nf6 $1) 16.
Re1 Qc6 $2 17. c4 $16 Qc7 18. Kg1 Kf8 19. Rg3 (19. d5 $1 e5 20. h5 $1 g5 21.
Nfd2 {[%csl Rf5][%cal Gg2g4]} f5 22. Nc3 f4 (22... g4 23. Rg3 $18) 23. Bf5 $18)
19... Re8 20. Qd2 Nf6 21. d5 Nh5 22. dxe6 Nxg3 23. exf7 Kxf7 24. fxg3 d5 25.
cxd5 Bxd5 26. Rc1 Bc5+ 27. Nxc5 bxc5 28. Bxg6+ Kxg6 29. Qxd5 Qxg3 30. h5+ Kg7
31. Qd7+ Kf6 32. Rf1 Rhf8 33. Nd4+ Kg5 34. Rf5+ 1-0

