{A good win for White with the Miladinovic attack! Black castled prematurely!} 
1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. Bg5 c5 4. e3 cxd4 5. exd4 b6 6. Nbd2 Bb7 7. Bd3 Be7 (
7... h6 {may only hurt Black after} 8. Bh4 Be7 9. Bxf6 Bxf6 10. Qe2 {Now,
castling kingside runs into h4-g4-g5.}) 8. c3 O-O $6 {Against premature
castling the Miladinov attack works well. Black should have played 8...d6.} (
8... d6 9. Bxf6 Bxf6 10. Qe2 Nd7 11. O-O-O Be7 12. Kb1 a6 13. h4 Nf6 14. Ka1
Nd5 15. g3 O-O 16. Bb1 b5 17. Qd3 g6 18. h5 Kg7 19. Rh3 Rh8 20. h6+ Kf8 21.
Rhh1 Bf6 22. Rhe1 (22. Rhe1 Ke7 23. g4) (22. g4) (22. c4 bxc4 23. Nxc4) (22.
Ne4) 22... Ke7 23. Ne4 Re8 24. Neg5 (24. g4 Bh8 25. Neg5) 24... Rh8 25. Qe2 Qd7
26. Ne4 (26. Be4)) 9. Bxf6 $1 Bxf6 10. Qe2 {Theoretically Black is doing OK,
but practically White has the much easier game!} d6 11. O-O-O $14 {White is
better with good attacking chances!} e5 $2 {Black opens the position while
being underdeveloped.} 12. dxe5 dxe5 13. Ne4 $16 Nc6 14. h4 Qe7 15. g4 {
White's attack plays itself.} g6 16. h5 $3 Bg7 (16... g5 17. Ng3 $18 (17. h6))
17. hxg6 fxg6 (17... hxg6 18. Nfg5 a6 19. f4 $1 (19. f3 $18 {[%cal Ye2h2]})
19... exf4 (19... Rfd8 20. f5 $18) 20. Rh8+ $3 Bxh8 21. Qh2 f6 22. Bc4+ Rf7 23.
Qh7+ Kf8 24. Qxh8#) 18. Bc4+ Kh8 19. Rxh7+ $1 Kxh7 20. Nfg5+ Kh8 21. Rh1+ Bh6
22. Rxh6+ Kg7 23. Rh7# 1-0

