{A good blitz game by black (by me), showing many typical ideas of the Polish
Variation!} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 b5 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. O-O c5 6. dxc5 $6 Bxc5
7. Nbd2 O-O 8. a4 (8. Re1 $4 Bxf2+ $1 9. Kxf2 Ng4+ 10. Kg1 Ne3 $19) (8. c4 bxc4
(8... a6) 9. Nxc4 d5 10. Nce5 Nbd7 $11) (8. b3 d5 9. Bb2 Nbd7 10. c4 dxc4 11.
bxc4 b4 $15) 8... b4 9. Nb3 Be7 $15 {Black is already better because White has
absolutely no pawn play!} 10. Bf4 (10. Bg5 Na6 11. Qd3 {SOS! Now we have to
watch out for tricks connected to Ng5!} Qc7 $1 (11... d5) ({But not} 11... h6
$4 12. Bxf6 Bxf6 13. Ng5 $16) (11... Qc8 $1 $15) 12. Bxf6 (12. h4 Rab8 {
I am entering a random move, just to point out that White has no threat:} 13.
Bxf6 Bxf6 14. Ng5 g6 (14... Bxg5)) 12... Bxf6 13. Ng5 {Now this trick no
longer works since b7 is protected.} Bxg5) 10... d6 (10... Na6 {is once again
playable since the blockading move} 11. Bd6 {is not all dangerous.} Bd5 ({or} 
11... Bxd6 12. Qxd6 Ne4 13. Qd4 d5) 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. Qd3 Nc5 14. Nxc5 Qxc5 $15
) 11. Re1 Na6 12. Bg5 h6 13. Be3 Qc7 14. Nfd4 Bxg2 15. Kxg2 Ng4 16. Bc1 Rac8
17. f3 Ne5 18. e4 Qb7 19. Nb5 Rfd8 20. Qe2 Nc5 21. Bf4 Ng6 22. Be3 e5 $5 $17 {
Black is threatening to win the b5-knight with ...a6.} 23. Nxc5 $6 dxc5 {
[%csl Rb5][%cal Ya7a6] Now White's knight is trapped!} 24. Red1 a6 $19 25. c4
axb5 26. axb5 Nf8 27. Rd5 Ne6 28. Rxe5 Nd4 29. Qf2 Bf6 30. Rd5 Rxd5 31. exd5
Re8 32. Re1 Qd7 33. Bxd4 Bxd4 34. Qd2 b3 35. Rxe8+ Qxe8 36. Qd3 Qe1 37. d6 Kf8
{'} 38. b6 Qb4 39. Qe4 Qxb6 40. Qe7+ Kg8 41. Qe8+ Kh7 42. Qe4+ g6 43. Qe7 Kg7
44. g4 Bf6 45. Qd7 Bxb2 46. h4 Bd4 47. g5 hxg5 48. hxg5 b2 49. Qe7 b1=Q 50. d7
Q6b2+ 51. Kh3 Qh1+ 52. Kg4 Qbg2+ 53. Kf4 Qxf3# 0-1

