1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 b5 4. Qd3 a6 ({or} 4... Ba6) 5. e4 Bb7 6. e5 (6. Nbd2
c5) 6... Nd5 7. Bg2 d6 (7... c5 $1 {was even better, with good counterplay.})
8. O-O Nd7 {Thanks to the pawn on b5, our d5-knight is stable - Black has good
play.} 9. a3 c5 10. dxc5 Nxc5 {I agree with this choice! We should avoid the
symmetrical pawn structure after ...dxc5.} 11. Qe2 dxe5 12. Nxe5 Bd6 13. b3 Qc7
14. Bb2 O-O 15. Nd2 Ne7 16. Bxb7 Qxb7 17. Rfd1 Rac8 18. Ndf3 Qe4 19. Qd2 Bxe5
20. Nxe5 f6 21. Nd7 Rfe8 22. Re1 Qd5 23. Qxd5 Nxd5 24. Nxc5 Rxc5 25. Rac1 Kf7
26. c4 bxc4 27. bxc4 Ne7 28. Red1 Rec8 $17 29. Rd7 Rxc4 30. Rxc4 Rxc4 31. Ra7
Rc2 32. Bd4 Rc6 33. a4 e5 34. Be3 Ke6 35. a5 g5 36. Bb6 g4 37. Rxa6 f5 38. h3
h5 39. Ra8 f4 40. gxf4 exf4 41. Rh8 Rc1+ 42. Kh2 Nd5 43. Rh6+ Kd7 44. Rxh5 Nxb6
45. axb6 Rc2 46. Rh7+ Ke6 47. hxg4 Rxf2+ 48. Kh3 Rb2 49. Rb7 f3 50. g5 f2 51.
Kg2 Kf5 52. Rb8 Kg6 53. b7 Kg7 1/2-1/2

