1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 b5 4. Bg2 (4. Bg5 Bb7 (4... Be7) 5. Bxf6) 4... Bb7 5.
Bg5 {In my opinion this is the best way to play against 3...b5 - play an early
Bg5!.} Be7 6. O-O Na6 7. Nbd2 c5 8. c3 cxd4 $6 9. cxd4 h6 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. a4
$1 b4 12. Nb3 $16 {White has a clear advantage already.} O-O 13. Qd3 d5 14.
Rfc1 Qb6 15. Qb5 Rac8 16. e3 Nb8 17. Bf1 Rfd8 18. h4 g6 19. Nc5 Bc6 20. Qd3 Ba8
21. a5 Qd6 22. Qb5 Kg7 23. Qxb4 Nc6 24. Qd2 e5 25. b4 Re8 26. Ra3 exd4 27. Nxd4
