1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 b5 4. Bg5 Bb7 5. Bg2 Be7 6. Nbd2 d6 {Black's lack of
experience in this line shows immediately.} (6... c5 $1 {is the best move.}) 7.
c4 $1 bxc4 8. Nxc4 O-O 9. O-O h6 $6 {A mistake, since I probably would have
taken on f6 anyway.} 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. Qd2 {Another good move - I prevent ...
a5 and threaten to annoy him with Na5.} (11. Rc1 a5) 11... Nc6 12. Rac1 Rb8 $6
(12... a5) 13. Rfd1 $14 Ba8 14. b3 Re8 15. e3 {I have an advantage and
stabilize my position.} Be7 16. h4 {Another good move, intending h4-h5 to fix
the structure.} Bf8 17. Na5 Rb6 18. Nc4 Rb5 19. Nb2 Rb6 $6 20. Ne1 d5 21. Na4
Rb8 22. Nd3 Ba3 23. Rc2 Qd6 24. Qc3 Re7 25. Nac5 Nb4 $6 (25... a5 $1 $14) 26.
Nxb4 Bxb4 27. Qb2 Rbe8 (27... Bxc5 28. Rxc5 e5 29. Qa3 $3 a6 30. dxe5 $16) 28.
Nd3 Ba5 29. b4 Rb8 30. Rb1 c6 31. Qa3 Bd8 32. Qc1 Bb7 33. Rb3 Rc7 34. Bf1 $1
$16 Bc8 35. Rbc3 Bd7 36. a3 (36. Nc5 Rxb4 37. Na6 Rb6 38. Nxc7 Qxc7 (38... Bxc7
39. Qa3 $16) 39. Qa3 Be8 40. Rb3 $16) 36... a5 37. bxa5 Ra7 38. Ne5 $5 $16 (38.
Rxc6 $3 Bxc6 39. Rxc6 Qf8 (39... Qe7 40. a6 $16) 40. a6 Rb6 (40... Be7 41. a4
Rba8 42. Ne5 Bd6 43. Qb2 $18) 41. Ne5 $16) 38... Rxa5 (38... Bxa5 39. Rxc6 Bxc6
40. Nxc6) 39. Rxc6 Bxc6 40. Nxc6 Rc8 41. Nxa5 Rxc2 42. Qxc2 Bxa5 43. Qa4 $1 Qd8
44. h5 $1 $16 {This is a complex technical endgame, in which my opponent
defended extremely well and gave me no real chance to win!} Kf8 45. Qc2 Ke7 46.
a4 Qc7 47. Qb1 $6 (47. Qh7 Kf6 48. Kg2 $16 Qc1 49. Bb5 Qb2 50. Qg8 Qc2 51. Be8
Qc7 52. g4) 47... Qc3 $1 48. Qb8 Qc7 49. Qh8 $4 (49. Qg8 $4 Qc2) (49. Qb1 $1
Qc3 50. Kg2 Qb4 51. Qh7 Kf6 52. Bb5 Qb2 53. Qg8 Be1 54. Qd8+ Kf5 55. Bd3+ Kg4
56. Qh4#) 49... Qc2 50. Qb8 Be1 51. Qf4 Qxa4 52. Qc7+ Qd7 53. Qc5+ Qd6 54. Qa7+
Kf6 55. Qa8 Bb4 56. Qa1 Qc7 57. Qd1 Ke7 58. Qb1 Qc3 59. Kg2 Kf6 60. Qh7 Bf8 61.
Be2 Qb3 62. Bf3 Bd6 63. e4 dxe4 64. Qxe4 Qb5 $1 (64... Ke7 65. Qg4 Kf8 66. d5
exd5 67. Qd7 Qb8 68. Bxd5 Be7 69. Qf5 Bf6 $11) 65. Qe3 Ke7 66. d5 e5 67. Qe4
Qb4 68. Qh7 Qd4 69. Qe4 1/2-1/2

