1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. g3 b5 4. Bg2 Bb7 5. O-O Be7 6. Bg5 d5 7. Bxf6 Bxf6 8. c3
Nd7 9. Nbd2 c5 10. dxc5 $6 Nxc5 {Now Black is better.} 11. Nb3 Na4 $1 $17 12.
Qd2 O-O 13. Nfd4 Qb6 14. e3 Rfd8 15. f4 {White wants to stop ...e5, but
creates weaknesses.} Be7 16. a3 a6 {A useful move, just protecting b5. Black
waits for a good moment to play ...a5-b4.} 17. Rfe1 Rac8 18. Qf2 Qc7 19. Re2
Nb6 20. Nc1 Nc4 21. Nd3 Nd6 22. Qe1 a5 {After some manoeuvering with his
pieces, Black finally starts to prepare the break ...b4.} 23. Qd1 Ba6 24. Bf1
Qb6 25. Rc2 Re8 26. Kh1 Bf8 27. Rac1 Rcd8 28. Bg2 g6 29. Ra1 Bg7 30. Qe2 b4 $1
$19 {At last the pawn break is executed - Black is already strategically
winning.} 31. axb4 axb4 32. Qd1 Bxd3 33. Qxd3 Ra8 34. Rcc1 bxc3 35. bxc3 Rxa1
36. Rxa1 Rb8 37. Bf3 Qb2 38. Rd1 Bxd4 39. cxd4 Rb3 40. Qd2 Qa3 41. Qf2 Rxe3 42.
Kg2 Rb3 43. Rd2 Nc4 44. Re2 Qc1 45. Kh3 Qc3 46. Bg2 Qd3 47. Bf1 Ne3 0-1

