Be7 15. Rb1 Nb4 16. Re1 a5 $17) 7... Be7 8. Nbd2 O-O 9. Qb1 {WHEN YOU SEE THE
QUEEN on the b1-h7 diagonal, White is quite often threatening 1.Bxf6-Bxf6 2.
Ng5! The way to defend against this threat is usually to protect the Bb7!} (9.
a4 b4 10. Re1) 9... Rb8 $1 10. e4 h6 $1 $13 11. Bxf6 (11. Bf4 Rc8 $13) 11...
Bxf6 $132 12. e5 $6 {Now Black is better because he will break with ...d7-d6!}
Be7 13. Ne1 cxd4 14. cxd4 d6 $17 15. Bxb7 Rxb7 16. Qe4 Rd7 17. exd6 Rxd6 18.
Nb3 Bf6 19. Nf3 Qb6 20. Rac1 Rfd8 21. Rc3 Nb4 22. Ne5 (22. a3 Nc6 23. Rfc1 Nxd4
24. Nbxd4 Bxd4 25. Rc6 Rxc6 26. Rxc6 Bxf2+ 27. Kg2 Qe3 $19) 22... Rd5 $1 (22...
Nxa2 23. Rf3 Nb4 $17) 23. a3 $6 Bxe5 24. dxe5 Nc6 25. Rfc1 Nxe5 26. Rc8 Nc4 0-1

